SUMMARY:Special Event -Stairs and Arches- location workshop with Drew G
DESCRIPTION:The Toronto Photography Group\nAbout the event\n\n11 am-1pm pm
  session\nStudio by House 1585 Britannia Road East L4W2M4\nLighting tech t
 bd\nModel Drew Gilder -[https://www.instagram.com/theonlydrewcatherine/?hl
 =en](https://www.instagram.com/theonlydrewcatherine/?hl=en)\nJoin us for t
 his fun and educational location lighting workshop with Drew G\, This will
  be a fun evening at Studio by House in Mississauga\n\n**Workshop Details:
 ** This is an amazing opportunity to light and shoot an talented glamour m
 odel in a wonderfully styled studio with some beautiful 3\,4 and 5 light s
 et ups with Elinchrom modifiers . We will be creating 3x lighting set ups 
 and creating some great art nude images using modifiers to soften and shap
 e the light .\nDo you aspire to learn the secrets of beautiful and creativ
 e soft and crisp lighting techniques on location?\nWe are dedicated to lig
 hting and sharing our photographic knowledge with you. Our fun and informa
 tive group workshop with professional instructors is designed to cater to 
 your interests. Throughout the workshop\, we will discuss the specific lig
 hting setups for each scenario\, explaining the choice of modifiers and an
 gles to effectively illuminate the subject and accessories.\n\nStudio by H
 ouse -\n\n\\*\\*Instructor:\\*\\*Phil Sutherland **Assistant:** tbd **Mode
 l:** The exceptionally awesome Drew Gilder. Her remarkable posing skills w
 ill contribute to creating stunning images during the workshop.\nTo ensure
  a high-quality experience for participants\, we are limiting the 2 hour w
 orkshop to a maximum of 8 participants.\n\nAs an indigenous-led\, not-for-
 profit arts group\, we are dedicated to serving the artistic community and
  advocating for the photographic arts. At our core\, we believe in sharing
  knowledge and the joy of photography with the community. We strive to mak
 e art accessible to everyone and work hard to bring arts programming to th
 e community.\n\n**Workshop Details:**\n\n* Maximum Participants: 8\n* Work
 shop Fee: CAD$97 plus hst and vendor fee\n\n**Items to Bring:**\n\n* Camer
 a/Lenses of choice (DSLR\, medium format\, or mirrorless)\n* Fully charged
  battery\n* Freshly formatted memory card(s)\n* General lenses\n* Pen and 
 paper (if you wish to take notes)\n\nSo that you know\, tripods or camera 
 supports are not required for this workshop.\n**Triggers:** We provide wir
 eless triggers for most mainstream camera types. Please feel free to email
  us to confirm compatibility with your camera.\n**Model Release:** A West 
 Toronto Photography Group model release form\, will be provided to each pa
 rticipant for non-commercial use and training purposes. The model will sig
 n these forms\, and printed copies will be provided to each photographer.\
 n**Cancellation Policy:** Refunds will be issued within 72 hours if we\, a
 s organizers\, have to postpone or cancel the event. We understand that so
 metimes circumstances prevent attendance at a workshop. If you cannot atte
 nd\, please get in touch with us as soon as possible\, and we will help yo
 u resell your workshop spot to the group. We will reimburse you for the ti
 cket price if we can resell the ticket. However\, if we cannot resell the 
 spot\, you may transfer it to someone else to attend in your place\, but u
 nfortunately\, no refund will be provided.\nWe look forward to welcoming y
 ou to this inspiring workshop and helping you enhance your photography ski
 lls .
